==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Queensland nut
<hw>Queens"land nut`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>The nut
of an Australian tree (<spn>Macadamia ternifolia</spn>). It is about an
inch in diameter, and contains a single round edible seed, or sometimes
two hemispherical seeds. So called from <xex>Queensland</xex> in
Australia.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Queen truss</ent>⟦br⟧
